commit.message:
[python] Fix snowballstemmer.algorithms() method

Fixes https://github.com/snowballstem/snowball/issues/132, reported
by kkaiser.

serbian.sbl: Replace R2 and p3 with boolean flag

R2 isn't really a region, but rather a yes/no test for diacritics.
The algorithm description even notes this, so let's just make it
a boolean which is clearer and possibly a little more efficient
in some languages.
serbian.sbl: Simplify mark_regions
serbian.sbl: Remove trailing whitespace

[python] Remove the classifiers blacklist

Basque, Irish and Nepali were added as possible natural languages to PyPI.
Fix typo in old NEWS entry

Fix mixed declarations and code

We aim for the code to compile as C90, but GCC and clang both accept
mixed declarations and code as an extension even under -std=c90.

Add -Wdeclaration-after-statement to the CI builds to catch
regressions in this.

Add str_append_b_tail() and use it for go

This avoids having to copy a string just to append all but its
first character.
Use const qualifiers more

[python] Remove Lithuanian from classifiers blacklist

See https://github.com/pypa/warehouse/issues/7047#issuecomment-560366145

[serbian] Simplify setting of R1

Combine some integer tests and eliminate sbst variable completely.

serbian: Initialise sbst to 0

This only matters for an input word which contains an 'r' and no
vowels, but we might see such cases from acronyms or typos.

This change probably makes no difference to the output, as all the
suffixes we might remove contains vowels.
Use const pointers more in C runtime

-parentclassname is not only for java and csharp

So don't disable it if those backends are disabled.

Store booleans in same array as integers

This means each boolean is stored as an int instead of an unsigned char
which means 4 bytes instead of 1, but we save a pointer (4 or 8 bytes)
in struct SN_env so that's a win for all the current stemmers.

For an algorithm which uses both integers and booleans, we also save the
overhead of allocating a block on the heap, and potentially improve
data locality.

Eliminate variables whose values are never used

They no longer have corresponding member variables, etc, and
no code is generated for any assignments to them.

CONTRIBUTING.rst: Add more advice on new generators

Point out that bindings are another option, and may be a better
solution.

Don't warn for grouping only used to define others

Suppress the "grouping X defined but not used" warning we were issuing
in this case.
Don't generate anything for an unused grouping

Stop numbering groupings internally

This numbering isn't actually used anywhere!

Stop writing comments by default

The comments in the generated code are useful if you're trying to
debug the compiler, and perhaps also if you are trying to debug your
Snowball code, but for everyone else they just bloat the code
which as the number of languages we support grows becomes more
of an issue.
Consistently use false/true for amongvar_needed
Eliminate duplicate C comment for sliceto

Remove unnecessary check in generate_setlimit()

p->left->right will always be NULL for a c_setlimit node.

snowball/stemwords: do link with LDFLAGS set by build-system

Some (cross-)build systems as OpeneEmbedded are picky (for certain reasons) if
their LDFLAGS are ignored.

Signed-off-by: Andreas Müller <schnitzeltony@gmail.com>

Minor optimisation to kraaij_pohlmann

Use `$v = limit` instead of `do (tolimit setmark v)`, which generates
simpler code, and matches the code other algorithm implementations use.

Probably for languages like C with optimising compilers the compiler
will generate equivalent code anyway, but e.g. for Python this should be
an improvement.
Update COPYING to include my own contributions

Merge Python backend licence into COPYING

Suggested by mitya57 in #119.
Fix comment typo

Python packaging updates
